<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-06-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-06-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="1547" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1547">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/611.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to Special Agent <persName type="to">Silliman</persName></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-07">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 7, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Consul, Mazatlan, reports Mazatlan Water Works confiscated May 24.
                                Reported Electric Company will be confiscated near future. Americans
                                interested these companies. Make vigorous protest to General
                                Carranza against confiscation these properties and request him order
                                restoration water works.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>